{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindingprotocol"]}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"BindingProtocol","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Whenever the source property changes, the same value is applied to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"target property; for instance, the following binding:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["  g_object_bind_property (object1, \"property-a\",","                          object2, \"property-b\",","                          G_BINDING_DEFAULT);"],"syntax":"c"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"will cause the property named “property-b” of "},{"code":"object2","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to be updated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"every time [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.set"},{"type":"text","text":"] or the specific accessor changes the value of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the property “property-a” of ","type":"text"},{"code":"object1","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is possible to create a bidirectional binding between two properties"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of two ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, so that if either property changes, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"other is updated as well, for instance:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["  g_object_bind_property (object1, \"property-a\",","                          object2, \"property-b\",","                          G_BINDING_BIDIRECTIONAL);"],"syntax":"c","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"will keep the two properties in sync."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also possible to set a custom transformation function (in both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"directions, in case of a bidirectional binding) to apply a custom","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"transformation from the source value to the target value before"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applying it; for instance, the following binding:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["  g_object_bind_property_full (adjustment1, \"value\",","                               adjustment2, \"value\",","                               G_BINDING_BIDIRECTIONAL,","                               celsius_to_fahrenheit,","                               fahrenheit_to_celsius,","                               NULL, NULL);"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"will keep the “value” property of the two adjustments in sync; the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"celsius_to_fahrenheit"},{"text":" function will be called whenever the “value”","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"property of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"adjustment1"},{"text":" changes and will transform the current value","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of the property before applying it to the “value” property of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"adjustment2"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Vice versa, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fahrenheit_to_celsius"},{"type":"text","text":" function will be called whenever"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the “value” property of "},{"code":"adjustment2","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" changes, and will transform the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"current value of the property before applying it to the “value” property","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"adjustment1"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Binding","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" does not resolve cycles by itself; a cycle like"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["  object1:propertyA -> object2:propertyB","  object2:propertyB -> object3:propertyC","  object3:propertyC -> object1:propertyA"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"might lead to an infinite loop. The loop, in this particular case,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be avoided if the objects emit the "},{"code":"GObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"notify","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":" signal only if the value has effectively been changed. A binding is implemented using the `GObject`notify"},{"type":"text","text":" signal, so it is susceptible to all the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"various ways of blocking a signal emission, like [func"},{"code":"GObject.signal_stop_emission","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.signal_handler_block"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A binding will be severed, and the resources it allocates freed, whenever"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"either one of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instances it refers to are finalized, or when","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Binding"},{"text":" instance loses its last reference.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Bindings for languages with garbage collection can use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.Binding.unbind","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] to explicitly release a binding between the source"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and target properties, instead of relying on the last reference on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"binding, source, and target instances to drop.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBinding"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Binding"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"pr